response: "{ \"title\": \"Easy: Sum of Squares\", \"description\": \"A company has N employees, and each employee can have at most one manager. Write a function `sum_of_squares` that calculates the sum of squares of all employee IDs.\\n\\n#### Function Signature\\n```python\\ndef sum_of_squares(employees: list[int]) -> int:\\n```\\n\\n#### Input\\n- `employees` (list[int]): A list of N integers representing employee IDs.\\n\\n#### Output\\n- Returns the sum of squares of all employee IDs.\", \"code\": \"def sum_of_squares(employees: list[int]) -> int:\\n    return sum(i ** 2 for i in employees)\", \"tests\": [\"assert sum_of_squares([1, 2, 3, 4, 5]) == 55\", \"assert sum_of_squares([-1, -2, 0, 0, 1]) == 6\", \"assert sum_of_squares([]) == 0\"] }"
